2.00	Kromdraai	Kromdraai, Gauteng	Kromdraai is a protected conservancy in western Gauteng, South Africa not far from Krugersdorp. Its name is derived from Afrikaans meaning "Crooked Turn" after a kink in the meandering Crocodile River.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/77/Blank_map_of_Gauteng_%282011%29.svg/284px-Blank_map_of_Gauteng_%282011%29.svg.png
